@startuml fig-tcp-connect-scan
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title TCP Connect Scan — Three Possible Outcomes

participant "Scanner\n(port_scanner.py)" as SC #FFE0B2
participant "Target Host" as TH #E3F2FD

== Port OPEN (service listening) ==

SC -[#1565C0]> TH : SYN (connect attempt)
TH -[#43A047]-> SC : SYN-ACK (accepted)
SC -[#1565C0]> TH : ACK (connection established)
SC -[#1565C0]> TH : RST (scanner closes immediately)

== Port CLOSED (no service) ==

SC -[#1565C0]> TH : SYN (connect attempt)
TH -[#E53935]-> SC : RST (ConnectionRefusedError)

== Port FILTERED (firewall / no response) ==

SC -[#1565C0]> TH : SYN (connect attempt)
SC -[#FF9800]>x SC : timeout expires\n(socket.timeout)

legend right
  OPEN: full TCP handshake succeeds.
  CLOSED: target immediately rejects (RST).
  FILTERED: no response within the timeout
  (typically a firewall drops the SYN).
  A connect scan completes the full handshake
  unlike a SYN scan which stops after SYN-ACK.
endlegend
@enduml
